data.description: Upon entering this charming Princeton Heights brick home, you'll be impressed with the amount of space in the living and dining rooms. The refinished hardwood floors are gleaming. The kitchen, dining & sunroom provide plenty of space for your family to dine & entertain. The tall baseboards and 9' ceilings add to the beauty of this home! Every room has lots of windows for an abundance of natural lighting. Mudroom in the rear is great for shoes, coats, etc. The shed is perfect for storing bikes & lawn equipment. The unfinished walk-up basement has lots of room for storage. Off-street parking with 2 newer concrete parking pads is provided behind the level fenced backyard. Enjoy the views of the quiet tree-lined street from the covered front porch. Updates include HVAC, windows, kitchen, bathroom, electric panel and the roof is about 12 years old. This home is conveniently located near shopping, schools, public transportation & walking distance to many local restaurants. Come take a look!
